data.title: Taylor Swift disses Kanye West at the Grammy Awards during her acceptance speech
data.meta_description: The singer directs part of her album of the year acceptance speech towards Kanye West at the Grammy Awards.
data.text:
Taylor Swift dissed Kanye during her acceptance speech at the Grammy Awards.

She's the first woman to win album of the year twice and said it was for "all the young women out there".

She said: "There are going to be people along the way who will try to undercut your success or take credit for your accomplishments or your fame."

Her speech appears to be in response to Kanye West's lyric from his new album where he claims to have made Taylor Swift famous.

Watch Taylor Swift's album of the year acceptance speech, external

And the internet has had a field day at Taylor's diss with Gifs predicting how Kanye will respond.

One uses wrote: Kanye after Taylor Swift's speech , external

One tweeted: When Taylor Swift shaded Kanye , external

Another wrote: Twitter waiting for Kanye like... , external

And there was: when kanye hear taylor been throwing shots , external

It all comes from a line from Famous on Kanye's new album: The Life of Pablo.

Read what happened at the Kanye West album launch.

He raps: "I feel like me and Taylor might still have sex/Why? I made [her] famous."

And he claims to have had her blessing for the line as she "thought it was funny".

It refers to the MTV VMAs in 2009 when Kanye West interrupted Taylor Swift's acceptance speech.
